title: Bug 10593: Jar export should add ".jar" suffix if not specified
OB: When exporting a Jar file, if the user does not specify a file extension, the system does not add the ".jar" extension automatically. As a result, the exported file does not have the appropriate file extension.
EB: The system should automatically add the ".jar" file extension when exporting a Jar file if the user does not specify a file extension. This will ensure that the exported file has the correct file extension.
SR:
To reproduce this issue, follow these steps:
1. Open the Jar export dialog.
2. Specify the Jar file name without the ".jar" file extension.
3. Click on the export button.
4. Verify that the exported file does not have the ".jar" file extension.
